{
  "text": "where \u03c4 c is a constant delay, x 1 is a Gaussian random variable x 1 \u2208 N(\u03bc, \u03c3) with mean \u03bc and variance \u03c3 2 , x 2 is a uniformly distributed random variable on [a min , a max ], and q is a filtering coefficient. The values of all delays are bounded between zero and a maximum value, \u03c4 max . \u03c4 3 (t) describes a delay, which is partially random, but depends on its previous values. For example, Internet delays have been shown to be correlated due to queues in routers [CITATION_1] .",
